description: The conclusion of a 2-part story guest-starring Hitman! Mitch wants to continue his quest to discover the mysterious Lab that gave him the ability to resurrect -- but first he's got to stop Hitman from constantly killing him. There's lots of collateral damage as the Resurrection Man and Hitman get down to business. The hits just keep on coming, especially when Tommy decides he should help Mitch by shooting him some more. ...
name: Mano A Mano

description: The adventures of DC's strangest hero continue! The Creeper's greatest enemy, Proteus, has returned, and he's deadlier than ever! And since Proteus wants to open The Creeper up and find out what makes him tick, you can be sure The Creeper's none too pleased to see him. Then again, he might be, after all, he is crazy!
name: Straitjacket

description: Power Girl is formally inducted into the Sovereigns as the team buries one of their own!  It's a mournful Christmas for the Sovereigns, and things may only get worse when they discover that the Rapture, which destroyed all the original Sovereigns' homeworlds, may be en route to Earth.
name: Remembrance Day

description:
Nightwing goes on an urban safari as Man-Bat shows up to terrorize the streets of Blüdhaven. Meanwhile, a new tenant (who's an old enemy) moves into Dick Grayson's building. Note: This issue also contains a Wizard self-mailer for NIGHTWING #1/2, also available in Wizard #77, on sale in December.

Dudley Soames awakened from his coma and learned it was impossible to ever be "straight" again. After stopping two people trying to shoot the man-bat down, Nightwing visited Francie Langstrom. He promised that he'd bring her husband - Dr. Kirk Langstrom - the Man-Bat - home. He and Man-Bat were both shot down with tranquilizer by Deathstroke.
name: The Stalking Skies

description: Sue storm is targetted for death as the iconoclast cloes in! But why is she in danger? and will she survive?
name: Be it ever so humble...

description: Christmas brings Woody (in Eric's body) to a strange ritual--a vigil for one of his closest friends, killed some years before--and reignites Woody's overwhelming desire for vengeance. Meanwhile, Eric (in Woody's body) struggles to find a solution to their switched body dilemma, and wrestles with the decision of whether or not to tell Woody a long-kept secret.
name: Where the Streets Have No Name

description: Things are heating up at Shadowman's soiree by the bayou as the Judge crashes the party with a whole lot of mayhem. Meanwhile, Nettie and the Master Loa, Baron Samedi, have a deadly bet on Shadowman's future...if Mike goes Deadside, will Nettie be far behind?
name: The Hoodoo Bash, Part 2
The Cowboy

description: Steel's long-thought-dead brother has stolen Steel's flight boots, and he's taking over the nation's toughest street gang by outfitting them with boots of their own. How will Steel defeat his own brother and his army?
name: Invasion
The Risen: Hell: Canto XIII

volume.name: Solar, Man Of The Atom: Hell On Earth

description:
Overview
Fed up with the NSA, feeling as trapped by the scientists as he did by the aliens who transplanted his brain into his stone body, Ron Lithgow concocts a plan. Aided by scientist Maureen Vonnegut, the plan will not only free Lithgow, but alert the world of his plight. But Agent Stamberg has other ideas -- to keep Lithgow under his control, he's willing to use lethal force! The story of Concrete's origin has been told before, but not like this!

As the lunar hordes arrive to sweep across Africa and claim the Earth for their own, Tarzan calls upon his trickster side in the hope of scaring the Vagas back into space with an ancient enemy! But the chief of the Moon Men has a powerful hunger . . . a hunger that can only be sated with a bellyful of steel, or the blood of a jungle lord!
name: Tarzan vs. The Moon Men (Part 4 of 4)

description: Kitanamono, the feral agent of the Conspiracy of Eight, has stolen the sacred sword. Usagi, however, is right on his heels, and behind them both is the bounty hunter, Gen. Lord Noriyuki and Tomoe are also on the run from the Conspiracy's assassins and the Geishu traitor, but they seek refuge with a seemingly harmless farmer who turns out to be an old enemy of the Geishu Clan. Jei, the demonic swordsman, abandons Keiko and is mysteriously drawn into the deep forests, down half-hidden trails towards some unknown goal.
name: Grasscutter, Chapter 5: Ikeda

description: Dick travels to Africa where he meets a tribe and learns new fighting kills with them. He develops the new persona of Nightwing.
name: Book Three: Now You See 'Em

volume.name: The Batman Adventures: The Lost Years

description: Catwoman receives a bouquet of flowers from a mystery person claiming to know her true identity. She investigates while trying to shake the feeling she's being watched.
name: Shared Mentality

description: The Challengers look into an offshore oil rig that is pumping up anything but oil! Dredging the depths of the sea has unleashed an ancient terror that threatens the lives of everyone on the rig - and the world!
name: Inferno!

description: After the JLA destroys the latest return of the Construct in South America, evidence shows up that terrorists are heading toward the site of the fighting to pick up any technology that may have been left behind. Chase is sent to check on things and make sure nothing gets out that shouldn't. And she is even given some super powered backup from the Suicide Squad.
name: Letdowns

description: After the trouble on their vacation cruise, Kyle (Green Lantern) Rayner and Connor (Green Arrow) Hawke, and Wally are trying to prove the guilt of the three super-villains responsible for the disaster. But they are up against one amazing super-villain lawyer, who is out to clear these villains
name: Three of A Kind Part 3; Death at the Top of the World

volume.name: Green Lantern / Sentinel: Heart of Darkness

description: By going back into the past, the would-be dictator Tremain has succeeded in changing the present into a world where he's in charge. But time resents being messed with and starts trying to fix itself, leading to confusion and near disaster for everybody! "Devonian Age" part 2.
name: Time Out of Joint

description:
The war for heaven has begun, as Neron’s demons aide the cast aside angel Asmodel in claiming the silver city. The angels defend, and are aided by recently killed Zauriel and Martian Manhunter. The two heroes enter the fray, but Zauriel hesitates because Asmodel has stolen his true love, Shannon Coyne, and holds her hostage.
 
Back in the land of the living, the Justice League continues to try to resuscitate Martian Manhunter, while independently Jerry the nurse and Michael try to resuscitate Zauriel. Batman comes up with a plan, and, with Aztek and Flash’s help, manage to bring the Manhunter back to life. Unfortunately, this means Manhunter is no longer able to help defend heaven. Back amongst the living, Martian Manhunter tells the League of Asmodel and Neron’s plot. But now, Zauriel must face them alone.
 
Asmodel and the demons take the main tower, and challenge God. Zauriel arrives, and is sad to see that Asmodel doesn’t recognize the face of God when he sees it. Neron arrives, and we find out that this whole scheme was a way for Neron to corrupt and gain hold of Asmodel’s soul; that Neron never believed his scheme to work. The demons retreat with Asmodel’s soul, and Neron returns Shannon to Zauriel.
 
Zauriel is resuscitated by Jerry and Michael. In reward for defending heaven, the angels award Zauriel with the Aerie, a floating headquarters above Los Angeles, and a new suit of armor. Zauriel becomes God’s first sanctioned super-hero, and comes to terms with the fact that Shannon is truly in love with Jerry .
name: Revelations
Resistance The Secret Origin of Spark!

description: Bulletman is found not to be a spy. Cameos by Abin Sur and Sarge Steel.
name: Close Encounters: Lightning and Stars Part 4

description: Jesse prepares for his spiritual quest; Starr gathers his army; Cassidy falls off the wagon; The Saint arrives....
name: You And Me Against The World (War in the Sun Part 2)

description: The third part of the story. Robin follows Dava in Krasna-Volny on a mission he is not entirely sure he understands. However, it all becomes clear to him as well as the mystery to Dava's sweet Cinnamon and Vanilla aroma.
name: Kiss and Kill

description: Dreams of gold come to Wesley Dodds's waking world in the final chapter of the thriller, "The Cannon." England's man of mystery, The Cannon, and the Golden Age Sandman race to find the link between the rarest coin in America and a string of gangland-style killings. And how will Dian Belmont come to terms with Wesley's newfound jealousy?
name: The Cannon Act IV of IV

description: Part 3 of the 4-part "Lightning & Stars" crossover! It's the battle of Jack's life when he goes up against Captain Marvel. Possibly the most action-packed issue of Starman ever, this battle promises to be a doozy! Concludes in THE POWER OF SHAZAM! #36.
name: Lightning and Stars, Part Three

description:
In the first of three self-contained stories exploring different subcultures in the City, an acquaintance of Spider Jerusalem's opts to have his consciousness downloaded, so Spider watches him and discovers the bizarre, insular community of posthuman "foglets."

Spider tries to help his assistant Channon come to terms with her boyfriend's decision to transfer his consciousness into a sentient nanite cloud.
name: Boyfriend is a Virus

description: The Golden Age Flash and Wonder Woman travel to the 1940s where they join with the heroes of the Justice Society of America to learn the cause for Jays previously repressed memories of a World War II-era Wonder Woman. Also, Diana's frustration with the way of the gods continues to grow while the mystery of Donna Troy simultaneously deepens and unfolds.
name: Past Imperfect

description:
Nobody can locate Captain America's shield in the depths of the Atlantic Ocean! Will he be able to fight the evil Hydra without his most trusted weapon?

A terrorist takeover of the Smithsonian Natural History museum goes bad when two kids are caught in the crossfire. Cap saves them and is given an older shield, one he used during World War 2.
name: Museum Piece

description: Old friends Iron Fist and Luke Cage can’t see eye-to-eye in their treatment of Punisher. Who will win out in the end? Meanwhile, White Tiger and Thena make their triumphant escape from Exodus!
name: Conflict of Interest

description: Thanos attempts to steal the energies behind the machines that maintain the Savage Land. Ka-Zar battles him, staying alive only because the battle takes place in his home territory.
name: Urban Jungle (Chapter Four): Garden Of Evil!

description:
At night on the campus of Empire State University, a shadowy figure scales the wall of the Science Building, and breaks into a lab, while being watched by Blade the vampire slayer.  Inside, while Peter Parker burns the midnight oil, the janitor, Jose, makes his rounds.  Jose enters the lab where the intruder, a vampire, is injecting himself with some formula.  The vampire kills Jose and is soon confronted by Spider-Man.  The vampire leaps out the window to evade Spidey, but the hero overcomes the vampire and webs him to a lamppost, while Blade watches from a treetop. 
On Riker's Island, the vampire is being held in a cell, bound in a straight-jacket, but he is unable to transform into mist or a bat.  Blade, with the aid of allies among the guards, breaks the bloodsucker out.  Later, Blade stakes the creature out on the beach under the noonday sun, and tries to extract from him the reason he can survive in sunlight.   
That evening, after Jose's funeral, Peter and Mary Jane watch a news report about the jailbreak, and Peter recognizes the image of the suspected accomplice as Blade.  Peter decides he has to go to New Orleans, where Blade is based, to get to the bottom of things, and so hitches a ride on a truck bound for Louisiana. 
Fifty miles out from New Orleans, Blade transports the vampire, insisting that he will learn the nature of the mutagenic formula his captive injected, whether he cooperates or not.  The vampire responds that it is inevitable that vampires will rule humans.  At this, Blade loses his temper, stops the vehicle and slashes at the bloodsucker, cursing his kind for taking so many of those he's cared for.  The vampire becomes subdued, sorrowfully telling Blade he watched his wife and children killed by vampires. 
Later, as the vampire is strapped to a lab table while researchers examine him, Blade becomes curious about his captive's past.  The vampire explains he was once Henry Sage, a family man living in Austria in the late 18th Century.  He arrived home one night and found his loved ones dead, then was himself attacked by Dracula.  As Sage's tale ends, Spider-Man arrives and tackles Blade, asserting that he will see the vampire slayer and the killer of Jose back in jail.   
While Spidey and Blade scuffle, Sage makes his escape.  The two end their conflict and give chase, tracking Sage to a graveyard.  The vampire gets Spider-Man in his clutches and is about to bite him, when Blade hurls his silver knife into Sage's heart.  The creature thanks Blade, then disintegrates over the headstones of his family.
name: Sun-Walkers!

description: Quicksilver finds himself in dire straits when he becomes prisoner to the Inhumans! Will Maximus the Mad finally succeed in Pietro’s destruction? Scarlet Witch and Crystal stage a breakout for Luna, held captive by Medusa!
name: Mad City
Spider-Hunt Part 4: Something Goblin This Way Comes...

description:
Mia Colt has been launched into the future and it has changed the universe. The whole thing is a mixed up jumble of Christopher Pike's crew and James Kirk's crew. Number One is in Command of the Excelsior with Pavel Chekov and Nano. Pike is in command of the Enterprise A and his crew is Spock, Uhura, Saavik, Jose Tyler, Hikaru Sulu, and Moves With Burning Grace. Kirk is in command of the cargo ship Bounty with Scotty. The one really noticeable character that is missing is Leonard McCoy. He is not the Chief Medical Officer Gabrielle Carlotti is.

If Mia doesn't get back home in four days she will die. The problem is she has to go to a planet in Klingon territory. This leads to the set up for a major battle Against General Chang.
name: Futures

description: Tuvok is trapped, Captain Janeway is enraptured, Chakotay is jilted and B'Elanna is on the prowl! In the balance: the very existence of the U.S.S. Voyager!
name: Survival Of The Fittest, Part Two

description: With the Avengers and the Fantastic Four controlled by Baron Zemo, the Thunderbolts are the only ones left to save the world!
name: Endgame
Revenge

description:
Darkseid and Magneto have teamed up to conquer Marvel's Earth, while the JLA, the Avengers, the X-Men and the Young Heroes join forces to oppose them. As the heroes make plans to attack Asteroid M where Magneto, Darkseid and their respective minions are based, Access arrives with Redwing (an Amalam of Robin and the Angel). He explains how his abilities allow him to combine heroes to create "Amalgams".

Meanwhile, aboard Asteroid M, as bickering between Darkseid's forces and Magneto's Brotherhood grows into isolated scuffles, the two despots summon Virmin Vundabar and the Toad. Darkseid's cloaked ally lays his hands on the two lackeys with electrifying results. At this point, Magneto and Darkseid observe the Justice League Satellite approach them. The Satellite docks, and the Amalgams calling themselves the X-League burst in: Redwing, Captain America, Jr. (Captain America and Captain Marvel, Jr.), Green Goliath (Green Lantern and Giant-Man), Wonder Wasp (the Wasp and Wonder Girl), Thor-El (Superman and Thor), Jean Black (Marvel Girl and Black Canary) and Quick Freeze (Impulse and Quicksilver).

They are soon met by the Brotherhood of Evil Gods: Sabrebak (Sabretooth and Kalibak), Virmin Vundavort (Vundabar and the Toad), Kantique (Kanto and Mystique), Silverlance (Quicksilver and Devilance), Disastermind (Desaad and Mastermind), Red Lash (Scarlet Witch and Lashina) and Blobba (the Blob and Stompa).

While that battle rages in orbit, the heroes on Earth, overseen by Professor X, fight against the Female Furies and the Deep Six.

Aboard the Asteroid, as Access watches the battle go against the X-League, Darkseid and his hooded ally find him. Access tries to escape through a portal, but it is quickly closed by the ally who reveals himself to by a future self of Access who has joined Darkseid. They commence to fight and their struggle carries them through one amalgamated universe after another. Weakened, the present Access collapses, then realizes he can amalgamate with his future self. He does so and rejects Darkseid's offer to join him.

Darkseid then recalls Mantis and Juggernaut whom he'd assigned to abduct Access' girlfriend Ming. They begin to fight and when Darkseid strikes Juggernaut while hurling an epithet about mutants, Magneto attacks him. Darkseid grabs Magneto by the throat, while Access begins to separate the evil Amalgams. The Brotherhood confronts Darkseid, demanding he release their leader. He does so, dispatching the mutants to Earth.

Darkseid accedes to a draw, and removes his forces, returning to Apokalips. With the heroes victorious, Access returns them to their proper universes. He then seeks out Ming in the present and explains to her that he now belongs to both dimensions, and although he must now leave, he promises he'll be back.
name: Combined Forces!

description:
Gax's tale continues as the rebellious robots face a new danger in the form of a massive starship that puts their ship in peril.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    
 
Forced to flee the plucky troupe head for Klibbertot the mercantile capitol of the galaxy where they hope to find human help.. and for Gax thats the start of a beautiful friendship.

Francie wakes excited to her alarm clock in her neat and tidy little girls bedroom. Katchoo wakes in her messy room on a mattress on the floor and kicks the clock.  
 
Francine busies herself with getting ready. Katchoo has a cigarette in bed. 
 
Fran has a family breakfast and mom sees her off. Kat plays loud music in her locked bedroom, her mother shouts outside the door, she flicks the cigarette on the floor and jumps out the window leaving the stereo on. 
 
Fran's papers get blown out of her hand by Katina on the back of a boys bike. 
 
Freddie reads a poem in class he wrote entitled "The Breast" in a theatrical manor. Katina is asked for her poem, she asks to go last and the teacher indicates not doing her homework entales being sent to the principal for the third time and that would mean suspension. She produces a a solemn poem called "This Mask I Wear" that takes everyone aback. 
 
The play is in rehearsal and Francine's toga is not coving her ample form. Katina sits n the seats watching. Her boyfriend arrives and says theres a rumor she is gay, he teases her and she elbows him in the face. 
 
Later that night Katina taps on Fran's window and is impressed at all her nice things. She tells her shes beautiful, Fran returns the compliment and Katchoo heads home.
name: Prosody

description:
The Hornblower tries to catch a Leanhaun Sidhe in a bar but is interrupted by a pair of his fellow avatars, the Sun Twins. The three fight over their quarry and she escapes. Kevin Matchstick, arriving on the scene, berates them--they're supposed to fight evil, not each other. The Hornblower apologizes but the Sun Twins are unrepentant.

Kevin and Kirby Hero are attacked by hell-hounds coordinated by the Sprigginflints and the Pale Incanter. Then Kevin is forced into a fight with another avatar, the Dragonslayer. Kevin wins, but the Bat burns him for fighting a fellow hero. When they get back to their apartment, they find Isis, who has come to town to help, along with her two sisters.
name: Lay On, Macduff

description: Daredevil tries to solve the mystery of Mr. Fear, but only finds a few questionable characters. Meanwhile, Charlie listens to his killer instincts on Candice. Can Daredevil get to the core of Fear himself?
name: Weight Of The World
Search and Seizure

description: What if your best friend bit you on the face? What happened to Woody (in Eric's body)? This issue, we find out Eric's most closely guarded secret.
name: Roar

description: Tension and clashing interpersonal traits may yet prevent the JLA from becoming a truly cohesive unit, and that suits Vandal Savage and the group known as Locus just fine! Savage and Locus step up their plans to eradicate the JLA before the team can pose a true threat to their secret plan.
name: Guess Who?
Tremble In Fear-- For The Beast Hunts You!

person_credits.name: David Mack
person_credits.role: writer, editor, artist, penciler, letterer, inker, colorist

name: Finder
Xena: Warrior Princess vs Callisto

description:
The Sea Wolf kills another victim, and Aquaman goes to serve up justice. In the meantime, Triton kills his father Poseidonis and swears revenge on Aquaman.

Aquaman is called away from Poseidonis by several dolphins through The Clear to the scene of a murder, where the man's body was dumped in the ocean. Aquaman the places the man's body back on the ship, causing his killer Sea Wolf to fall overboard during which he begins to transform into his wolf form. They then begin a battle in the sea, with Aquaman plunging his harpoon into his foe's chest freeing dozens of trapped souls as the Sea Wolf floats to the bottom of the ocean.

While back in the city Tempest decides his fate is to run for High Councillor of Poseidonis. While back on the deck of the ship the Sea Wolf comes alive with the soul of his latest victim being the only one to remain. While elsewhere Triton attacks his father with his Triton as he criticizes him taking his power for himself with him setting his sights on Aquaman.
name: Necessary Poisons
Xena: Warrior Princess: The Orpheus Trilogy

volume.name: Xena: Warrior Princess: The Orpheus Trilogy

description:
Prometheus (now disguised as Retro) was teleported up to the Watchtower along with over one hundred members of the media (including Lois Lane and Martian Manhunter disguised as Clark Kent), who were to cover the re-formation of a new JLA, along with the introduction of several new members. Batman monitored everything in from the Monitor Womb, explaining that he can’t find anything wrong with Retro. The new JLA was quickly introduced, and a question and answer session commenced. ‘Retro’ feigned an upset stomach from going through the teleporter; Steel escorted him to the bathroom.

Once they were far enough away ‘Retro’ uploaded a virus into Steel’s armor, taking control of it; revealing himself to be Prometheus, he declared that: “I’m here to destroy the Justice League!” He then ordered Steel to walk far away and then to throw his hammer as far as he can.

SupermanJonn immediately realized something was wrong and went looking for Steel and Retro after informing Superman and Wonder Woman ( Hippolyta ). He instead found Prometheus downloading the blueprints of the Watchtower directly into his brain. Jonn ordered Prometheus to stand down and surrender. Prometheus responded by shooting Jonn with a phosphorous dart, and then as his powers were weakened, he shot him with a toxic dart that broke down chemical bonds, rendering Jonn the most powerful puddle of goo alive.

HuntressHaving lost their telepathic communication, the JLA went on high alert, as Prometheus set fire to garden which was responsible for most of the breathable air on the Watchtower and disabled the teleporters. Prometheus quickly dispatched Zauriel to the Ghost-Zone, and hypnotized Huntress before knocking her out. Batman then confronted Prometheus.

Prometheus quickly downloaded 30 of the worlds greatest martial artists into his brain (Batman being one of them), and set up a disorienting light pattern on his helmet to distract Batman as they engaged each other.

Green LanternFlash and Kyle Rayner began their search and found that main power was going offline, GL noted that he was having trouble concentrating as his construct flashlight began to discorporate. Prometheus is heard explaining that GL is having trouble concentrating because of an invention of his called the "Neural Chaff", which disorders conscience thought, making his power ring useless. However it does not work on Flash’s high frequency brain, so Prometheus goes on to explain that he has been planting motion sensitive bombs since he arrived, so that if Flash should go one iota above normal speed, every one of them will explode. He then dropped the unconscious form of Batman and declares “Five down, who wants to be number six?”
name: Camelot

description: When Dani's brothers become hopelessly ensnared in the First of the Fallen's media web, John Constantine must look for a solution in a most unlikely place. "Up the Down Staircase" part 3.
name: Up The Down Staircase, Part 3

description: Deadpool punishes Blind Al for her disobedience by putting her in "the hole". This brutal and sadistic punishment leads to a rift between them as AL realizes how far Deadpool has fallen.
name: In Absentia

description:
Gotham is besieged by a wave of hate crimes just as the eerie, mysterious Ragman returns to the city. Is he the culprit or a shabby force for justice?

The Ragman is out of control and the rags take a will of their own. A small gang of aryan reich nazis are in danger of being smothered for their hate crimes unless Batman and Rabbi Luria intervene in time.
name: The Greatest Evil

description: Hunting the one who "killed" him, the Spook knows that someone in the house is the one responsible for his death. And as Batman prepares to rip open the supernatural-seeming villain's shroud of secrets, he finds one person within the group is helping the Spook. "Spook" part 3.
name: Spook: Three of Three

volume.name: Batman: Legends of the Dark Knight

description: At Judge Napoleon's birthday bash the Societe is about to roast Shadowman alive. With her own soul on the line in a dangerous wager with Baron Samedi, Nettie turns to the Deadside to try to summon some help from beyond the grave.
name: The Hoodoo Bash, Part 3

description:
The team comes across the power-drained body of Wolverine. And standing over the body is Rogue. Is she truly to blame?

At Xavier's Mansion, Rogue wakes from a nightmare in which she absorbs Wolverine's powers then engages him in a fight to the death. Storm, who came by to invite Rogue to the pond with the rest of the team, comforts and assures her.

On the rooftop of his New York City home, Warren Worthington ponders his place in life, with or apart from the X-Men. Psylocke tests him by dropping off the roof, and he swoops down to catch her before she hits the pavement.

At the mansion, while the rest of the team prepare to walk down to the pond, Logan senses a stranger approaching and intercepts her. She is Margaret Stone an inspector for the school board, there to review the school, much to Logan's consternation.

In space, Deathbird watches over the severely injured Bishop as they continue their return to the Shi'ar Empire.

Inside Xavier's, Rogue visits Joseph who destroys his TV set after watching a news report on one Dr. Agee who claims he has a cure for mutations. She offers to absorb some of his mind to reconstruct his memories, but he rudely refuses, and she runs out of the mansion. Behind her, Joseph crumples in pain, yelling, "He is near!", just as Logan and Mrs. Stone pass by his room. Disapproving of the state of the building and the behavior of the 'students', she puts the school on probation and promptly leaves.

At the pond where storm has dispelled the winter cold so she and her teammates can enjoy some swimming, Logan rejoins the rest. Innocent horseplay takes a bad turn when Logan does not take kindly to being hit by Bobby Drake's snowball, and tackles him, both tumbling into the pond. Logan storms off, as Bobby realizes his leg suffered a cut on something metal under the water. The team discover the original Blackbird, scuttled years before.

As Logan lies on the ground apart from the rest, he comes under attack by someone who absorbs his mutant energy, and he lets out a scream that attracts his allies. They run to find Rogue kneeling over him, and assume she's responsible. Hurt by the accusation, she runs off as the real culprit, Sauron, reveals his presence.

In Alaska, Scott Summers and Jean Grey arrive at the Summers' cabin.
name: Blackbirds

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: Weatherman learns that the two rogue agents that Henry Bendix created years ago are on the move towards the Nevada Garden. Meanwhile, the demise of Apollo and Midnight's original team is revealed.
name: A Finer World: Part 2

deck: Supergirl goes ice skating, talks with God (a.k.a. Wally Johnson), fights a villain with vacuum-cleaner hands, and meets Comet for the first time.
description: Supergirl has a heart-to-heart with Wally, Jon Kent has a heart-to-heart with Fred Danvers, and Comet shows up and saves the day again.
name: Middle-Aged Crisis

description: Tenth and Hyena once again are plotting to get to Luse. Jace has taken Luse to the last person he could imagine to be healed.
name: Sanctuary Book 6: Cat and Mouse One: Here Kitty Kitty

story_arc_credits.name: Sanctuary Book 6: Cat and Mouse One: Here Kitty Kitty

first_appearance_storyarcs.name: Sanctuary Book 6: Cat and Mouse One: Here Kitty Kitty

description: Kyle, Wally, and Connor head out on an ocean cruise for some much needed R&R. However, these three young heroes soon find that there is no rest for the wicked as three super-villains have also made the trip.
name: Three of A Kind, Part 1
Slave of Heavens, Part 2: The Scale

description: Thanks to his recent encounter with Hitman, Mitch is crackling with power, and he's going to need it as he finally returns to the lab where the Resurrection Man was created. Finally, all the secrets of Mitch's origin are revealed, along with the secrets of Hooker!
name: Origin of Species, Part 1

description: Nightwing woke up hours later and updated Francine Langstrom on the situation with her husband. After meeting John Law, the man who used to be the superhero Tarantula, Tad got delusions of grandeur. Man-Bat was going to be exploited by a direct-to-video crew. Nightwing was able to free him, but he could not return him to his wife.
name: The Hunting Moon
Three Friends
The Boy; The Warrior; The Veteran

description:
Heroes Return. The Fantastic Four contend with the Red Ghost and the Super Apes, who are out for revenge in "Happy New Year, Reed Richards...Now Die!" Cameos by Silver Surfer, Alicia Masters, Crucible, Mole Man.

Notes:

  • Ranked #78 in Wizard Magazine's list of "100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born".
name: Happy New Year, Reed Richards... Now DIE!

concept_credits.name: 100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born

first_appearance_concepts.name: 100 Best Single Issue Comics Since You Were Born

description:
General Notes

As with all the other issues in this series, the title of the issue comes from the name of a Voudun "god", in this case the sky god, Damballah, creator of life. In the previous issues he was referred to as "Mr. D" and never seen, only heard pacing the floor in the attic of The Royale. In this issue he remains unseen although his presence is depicted as a resolution to the events involving Christian and his "deal with the devil".
name: Damballa

description: Finally, Quantum & Woody get returned to their rightful bodies. If you ask us, it's about time. Eric (or is it Woody, we're so confused) recruits the love of his life to join the team. Also, an absolutely major turning point in the lives of Eric and Woody.
name: Enough Already
The Killer

description: Steel has a heart--literally--and he has to fly it over to the Garden State Medical Center for someone awaiting a vital operation. Problems arise, however, when navigational controls in Steel's suit go haywire in a storm, and there's an assassin who's been hired to destroy the heart.
name: Heart

description: Tin soldiers and Nixon's orders--the Doctor is in Vietnam! Thirty years after Doctor Tomorrow teamed up with Gilad the War Master (in Operation: Stormbreaker), the two are fighting on the side of the Viet Cong?!! It's all out war action brought to you by the man himself, GIL KANE!
name: The Eternal Struggle

description: Solar confronts the original Solar, demanding he take the power back, and ends up confronting his own inner hell--the icky family secret he and his sister have carried all their lives. This secret in turn becomes the key to understanding Jimmy Six and defeating his nefarious plan.
name: Bang: Paradise: Canto XXVI

volume.name: Solar, Man Of The Atom: Hell On Earth

description:
Overview
Agent Stamberg starts to draw Concrete into the spy's shadowy, amoral world by means both subtle and brutal. Maureen tries to help Concrete resist, while Stamberg attempts to drive a wedge between the two. Then an eight-year-old's birthday and a coal mine disaster pull matters out of everyone's control. And you'll be knocked out by Concrete's first acquisition for his erotic art collection!

Usagi and Gen continue their pursuit of Kitanamono who, unbeknownst to them, has already had a run in with Jei. Who now has possession of the sword of the gods? Tomoe and Noriyuki are cornered by the assassins and are forced to rely upon an old enemy to save them. Even under Priest Sanshobo's care, Inazuma continues to sink closer to death.
name: Grasscutter, Chapter 6: Tomoe and Ikeda

description: Batman, after Dick leaving, becomes more brutal and in a worse mood, much to the concern of Batgirl. While hunting down Two-Face one night, Batman saves Tim Drake, the son of one of Two-Face's thugs. After Tim's father was killed, Tim swore revenge, Batman took him in and trained him as his new Robin.
name: Book Four: As the Tiwg is Bent

volume.name: The Batman Adventures: The Lost Years

description: "Cataclysm" part 6, continued from Detective Comics (1937-2011) #720. Catwoman is trapped in a collapsing department store, torn between her need to avoid an almost certain capture and her desire to help people who will die if she abandons them. Continued in Robin (1993-2009) #52.
name: Cataclysm 6: Claustrophobia

description:
The Challengers investigate an event stranger than any they've encountered to date as a thousand-foot-tall giant rises from the ocean depths!

A giant is stomping through England, stepping on every church in it's way. The problem is that too many villagers are gathering at churches to pray in response to the threat of the giant. It's a race against time to save people from being smashed.
name: Earth Came A-Walkin'

description: After almost dying at the hands of her "backup", Chase is captured by the people searching the Construct's base, the Russian mafia. While the Suicide Squad has a running fight with the Shining Path terrorists, Chase is forced to interface with some equipment left behind by the descruction of the Construct. Unfortunately, it seems the reports of its destruction are a bit premature.
name: Pickups
